The paper deals with the equivalence problem of tree transducers, which is a topic in formal language theory (FL) and logic (LO). The use of polynomial time algorithms suggests a connection to data structures (DS) and information theory (IT). Finally, the mention of parameters accumulating strings instead of trees suggests a connection to programming languages (PL).
